/*
# Explorer Toggle Details Pane

Toggle File Explorer panes by clicking empty space in the file list. In the
mod settings, pick per pane which mouse button toggles it: the left button
(double-click) or the middle/scroll wheel button (single click); each action
can also be disabled.

The details pane is toggled by sending `Alt+Shift+P`. For the navigation pane,
the mod toggles Explorer's per-tab `PageSpaceControlSizer_Visible` state.

## Windows version support

This mod targets 64-bit Windows 10 and Windows 11 File Explorer.
*/
// ==/WindhawkModReadme==

// ==WindhawkModSettings==
/*
- detailsPaneButton: left
  $name: Details pane mouse button
  $description: >-
    The button that toggles the details pane (sends Alt+Shift+P) when clicked
    on empty space
  $options:
  - left: Left button (double-click)
  - middle: Middle button (single scroll wheel click)
  - none: Disabled
- navigationPaneButton: middle
  $name: Navigation pane mouse button
  $description: >-
    The button that toggles the navigation pane when clicked on empty space
  $options:
  - left: Left button (double-click)
  - middle: Middle button (single scroll wheel click)
  - none: Disabled
*/
// ==/WindhawkModSettings==

